{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871320212,"sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2dcecf001U5sj1yKbfKYXIs","messageID":"msg_d7a2dc08f001jSvJCp1koa71UN","sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Changes to Existing Code\n4: \n5: ### New Files\n6: \n7: ```\n8: pkg/picod/\n9: ├── executor.go       # Core CommandExecutor implementation\n10: ├── executor_test.go  # Unit tests\n11: ├── types.go          # Request/response types\n12: ├── status.go         # Execution status management\n13: ├── output.go         # Output capture and streaming\n14: └── errors.go         # Error definitions\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### Interfaces Added\n18: \n19: ```go\n20: // pkg/picod/types.go\n21: \n22: type ExecutionID string\n23: \n24: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n25:     Command        string\n26:     Args           []string\n27:     WorkingDir     string\n28:     Environment    map[string]string\n29:     Timeout        time.Duration\n30:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n31:     SessionID      string\n32: }\n33: \n34: type ExecutionResult struct {\n35:     ID         ExecutionID\n36:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n37:     ExitCode   int\n38:     Stdout     []byte\n39:     Stderr     []byte\n40:     StartedAt  time.Time\n41:     FinishedAt time.Time\n42:     Error      *ExecutionError\n43: }\n44: \n45: type ExecutionStatus struct {\n46:     ID         ExecutionID\n47:     State      ExecutionState\n48:     StartedAt  *time.Time\n49:     FinishedAt *time.Time\n50:     ExitCode   *int\n51: }\n52: \n53: type ExecutionState string\n54: \n55: const (\n56:     StatePending    ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n57:     StateRunning    ExecutionState = \"running\"\n58:     StateCompleted  ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n59:     StateFailed     ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n60:     StateCancelled  ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n61: )\n62: \n63: type ResourceConstraints struct {\n64:     MaxMemory   int64         // bytes\n65:     MaxCPU      float64       // percentage\n66:     MaxIOBytes  int64         // bytes per second\n67:     MaxFiles    int\n68: }\n69: \n70: type ExecutionError struct {\n71:     Code    string\n72:     Message string\n73:     Details map[string]interface{}\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Dependencies\n78: \n79: - `pkg/sandbox` (AR-009): Sandbox interface for command execution\n80: - `pkg/store` (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014): For execution status persistence\n81: \n82: ### Configuration\n83: \n84: New configuration options:\n85: \n86: ```yaml\n87: picod:\n88:   default_timeout: 30s\n89:   max_concurrent_executions: 100\n90:   max_output_size: 10MB\n91:   output_buffer_size: 4KB\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ## API Surface\n95: \n96: ### Public API\n97: \n98: ```go\n99: // NewCommandExecutor creates a new PicoD command executor\n100: func NewCommandExecutor(sandbox SandboxClient, store StatusStore, opts ExecutorOptions) (*CommandExecutor, error)\n101: \n102: // Execute runs a command synchronously\n103: func (e *CommandExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n104: \n105: // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously\n106: func (e *CommandExecutor) ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n107: \n108: // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution\n109: func (e *CommandExecutor) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n110: \n111: // Cancel stops a running execution\n112: func (e *CommandExecutor) Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n113: \n114: // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output\n115: func (e *CommandExecutor) StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Behavioral Changes\n119: \n120: - Commands are now executed through PicoD API instead of direct sandbox calls\n121: - Resource limits are enforced at the API layer\n122: - All executions are tracked with persistent status\n123: - Output is captured and can be streamed\n124: \n125: ## Migration Notes\n126: \n127: - Existing direct sandbox usage should migrate to PicoD API\n128: - No breaking changes to sandbox interface\n129: - PicoD API is additive layer on top of existing components\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n\n## Changes to Existing Code\n\n### New Files\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── executor.go       # Core CommandExecutor implementation\n├── executor_test.go  # Unit tests\n├── types.go          # Request/response types\n├── status.go         # Execution status management\n├── output.go         # Output capture and streaming\n└── errors.go         # Error definitions\n```\n\n### Interfaces Added\n\n```go\n// pkg/picod/types.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871320183,"end":1775871320211}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871320214,"sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2dd33d001H8UH3QoOngmbjn","messageID":"msg_d7a2dc08f001jSvJCp1koa71UN","sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-014  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n23: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n24: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n26: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n27: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n31: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n32: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n36: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n37: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n38: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123` using `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n40: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n41: - **AND** return `nil` error\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n45: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n46: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error())` as true\n48: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n51: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n52: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n53: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n54: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n58: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n59: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n60: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n61: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n65: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n66: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n68: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n72: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n73: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n74: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n76: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic DoMulti\n79: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n80: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n81: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n82: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n83:   - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build()`\n84:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n85:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n86: - **AND** all commands SHALL succeed for the operation to complete\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n89: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n90: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n91: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n92: - **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists (return value other than \"OK\")\n93: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n97: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n98: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()`\n101: - **AND** return error indicating \"key not exists\" if key does not exist (result not \"OK\")\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n104: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n105: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists in Valkey\n106: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n107: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n108: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n109: - **AND** update the JSON value\n110: - **AND** return `nil` error\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session and indexes\n113: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` exists\n114: - **AND** `session:expiry` has member `sess-1`\n115: - **AND** `session:last_activity` has member `sess-1`\n116: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n117: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n118: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n119:   - `DEL session:sess-1` using `B().Del().Key(key).Build()`\n120:   - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n121:   - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n122: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n125: - **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n126: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n127: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n128: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n129: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n130: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n131: - **AND** return results ordered by expiry time (ascending)\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n134: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n135: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n136: - **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n139: - **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n140: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n141: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n142: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n143: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n144: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n145: - **AND** return results ordered by last activity time (ascending)\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n148: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n149: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n150: - **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity updates ZSET\n153: - **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n154: - **AND** current time is `now`\n155: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n156: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n157: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL first verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n158: - **AND** if exists returns 1, execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build()`\n159: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity returns ErrNotFound for missing session\n162: - **GIVEN** no session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n163: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n164: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n165: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n166: - **AND** when exists returns 0, return `ErrNotFound`\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time when at is zero\n169: - **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n170: - **AND** zero time `time.Time{}` is passed as `at` parameter\n171: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n172: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", time.Time{})` is called\n173: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()` as the activity timestamp\n174: - **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1`\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connections\n177: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connections\n178: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n179: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `s.cli.Close()`\n180: - **AND** return `nil`\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Valkey loadSandboxesBySessionIDs tolerates orphaned entries\n183: - **GIVEN** a list of session IDs from ZSET query including orphaned entries (no corresponding session key)\n184: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n185: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)` is called\n186: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `MGET` with all session keys using `B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()`\n187: - **AND** skip entries where `v.ToString()` returns error or empty string\n188: - **AND** return only valid sandbox entries without error\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### Requirement: Valkey Configuration\n193: \n194: The system SHALL read Valkey configuration from environment variables and create appropriate client options.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Valkey ADDR is required\n197: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n198: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n199: - **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR is required`\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Valkey ADDR supports multiple addresses\n202: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=\"host1:6379,host2:6379,host3:6379\"`\n203: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n204: - **THEN** return `InitAddress` as `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\", \"host3:6379\"}`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n207: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n208: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n209: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not set\n210: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n211: - **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n214: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n215: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n216: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n217: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n218: - **THEN** return options with empty password and no error\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option\n221: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n222: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n223: - **THEN** return options with `DisableCache: true`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option\n226: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n227: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n228: - **THEN** return options with `ForceSingleClient: true`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Valkey password parsing is case-insensitive for REQUIRED\n231: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE` or `False` or `false`\n232: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n233: - **THEN** treat as password not required\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Requirement: Provider Selection\n238: \n239: The system SHALL support runtime selection between Redis and Valkey backends via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE is unset\n242: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n243: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n244: - **THEN** default store type is `redis`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Select Valkey when STORE_TYPE=valkey\n247: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n248: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n249: - **THEN** create and return `valkeyStore` instance\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Reject unsupported store type\n252: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=unsupported`\n253: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n254: - **THEN** return error indicating `unsupported store type: unsupported (supported: redis, valkey)`\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Configuration\n259: \n260: ### Environment Variables\n261: \n262: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n263: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n264: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Storage backend type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n265: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey server addresses |\n266: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | - | Valkey authentication password |\n267: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n268: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n269: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Dependencies\n274: \n275: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` - Valkey Go client (v1.0.0+)\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Implementation Notes\n280: \n281: - Valkey is Redis-compatible, so the command patterns mirror Redis implementation\n282: - The `valkey-go` client uses a builder pattern (`B()`) for constructing commands\n283: - Pipeline/Multi operations use `DoMulti()` for atomic execution\n284: - Nil checks use `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` instead of `redis.Nil`\n285: - String results use `result.ToString()` instead of direct string conversion\n286: - Array results from `ZRANGEBYSCORE` use `result.ToArray()` then iterate with `v.ToString()`\n287: - MGET results use `result.ToArray()` and skip entries where `ToString()` returns error\n288: - All ZSET scores use Unix timestamp (seconds since epoch) as float64\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Key Differences from Redis Implementation\n293: \n294: | Aspect | Redis (go-redis/v9) | Valkey (valkey-go) |\n295: |--------|---------------------|-------------------|\n296: | Client creation | `redis.NewClient(opts)` | `valkey.NewClient(opt)` |\n297: | Command building | Direct methods | Builder pattern `B().Cmd().Build()` |\n298: | Pipelines | `Pipeline()` + `Exec()` | `DoMulti()` |\n299: | Nil check | `err == redis.Nil` | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` |\n300: | Get result | `.Result()` string | `.ToString()` on result |\n301: | Array result | Direct slice | `.ToArray()` then `.ToString()` |\n302: | Close | Returns error | Returns nil |\n\n(End of file - total 302 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871320188,"end":1775871320213}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871320217,"sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2dd7b5001he9P792XktHvLW","messageID":"msg_d7a2dc08f001jSvJCp1koa71UN","sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-013  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Redis Storage Implementation provides concrete implementations of the Store interface using Redis and Valkey as backends. It handles connection management, command execution, and backend-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Redis Store Implementation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Redis-backed Store implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` that satisfies the Store interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Redis Ping returns PONG\n22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server at `REDIS_ADDR`\n23: - **AND** a valid `redisStore` instance\n24: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n26: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n27: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Redis Ping fails on connection error\n30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Redis server\n31: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n32: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n36: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n37: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n38: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n40: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n41: - **AND** return `nil` error\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Redis\n45: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n46: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `redis.Nil` error\n48: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n51: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n52: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n53: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n54: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates input\n58: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n59: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n60: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n61: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n65: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n66: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n68: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n72: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n73: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n74: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n76: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n79: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n80: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n81: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n82: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n83:   - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n84:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n85:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n86: - **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n89: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n90: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n91: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n92: - **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL return `false`\n93: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n97: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n98: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n101: - **AND** when result is `false`, return error `key not exists`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n104: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n105: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists\n106: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n107: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n108: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n109: - **AND** return `nil` error\n110: - **AND** SHALL NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n113: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n114: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n115: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n116: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n117: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses atomic pipeline\n120: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n121: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n122: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n123: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n124:   - `DEL session:sess-1`\n125:   - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n126:   - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n127: - **AND** return `nil` error\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n130: - **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n131: - **AND** `limit = 10`\n132: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n133: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n134: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGE session:expiry -inf 1234567890 BYSCORE LIMIT 0 10`\n135: - **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n136: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n139: - **GIVEN** `limit = 0` (or negative)\n140: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n141: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n142: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes skips orphaned entries\n145: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains session ID `orphan-1`\n146: - **AND** key `session:orphan-1` does NOT exist\n147: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n148: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n149: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL skip `orphan-1` in results\n150: - **AND** return only valid sessions\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n153: - **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n154: - **AND** `limit = 10`\n155: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n156: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n157: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGE session:last_activity -inf 1234567890 BYSCORE LIMIT 0 10`\n158: - **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n159: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n162: - **GIVEN** `limit = -1` (or zero)\n163: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n164: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n165: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity rejects empty session ID\n168: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n169: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n170: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)` is called\n171: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n172: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity verifies existence\n175: - **GIVEN** session ID `unknown-sess`\n176: - **AND** key `session:unknown-sess` does NOT exist\n177: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n178: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-sess\", now)` is called\n179: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `EXISTS session:unknown-sess`\n180: - **AND** when result is `0`, return `ErrNotFound`\n181: - **AND** SHALL NOT update activity index\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time for zero\n184: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n185: - **AND** `at = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n186: - **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n187: - **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n188: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n189: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()`\n190: - **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Redis Close releases connection\n193: - **GIVEN** a `redisStore` instance with active connection\n194: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n195: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `cli.Close()` on the Redis client\n196: - **AND** return the resulting error (nil on success)\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n201: \n202: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n205: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n206: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n207: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n208: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command via `B().Ping().Build()`\n209: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n210: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n213: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n214: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n215: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n216: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n219: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n220: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n221: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n222: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n223: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n224: - **AND** return `nil` error\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n227: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n228: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n229: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n230: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `IsValkeyNil` error\n231: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n234: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n235: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n236: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n237: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n238: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n241: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n242: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n243: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n244: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n245: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n248: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n249: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n250: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n251: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n252: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n255: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n256: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n257: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n258: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n259: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses DoMulti\n262: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n263: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n264: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n265: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute via `DoMulti`:\n266:   - `SET session:sess-1 {json} NX`\n267:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n268:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n269: - **AND** check first result for \"OK\" indicating success\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n272: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n273: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n274: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n275: - **THEN** `SET NX` SHALL NOT return \"OK\"\n276: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n279: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n280: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n281: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n282: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n283: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n284: - **AND** when result is not \"OK\", return error `key not exists`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n287: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n288: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists\n289: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n290: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n291: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n292: - **AND** return `nil` error\n293: - **AND** SHALL NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n296: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n297: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n298: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n299: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n300: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti\n303: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n304: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n305: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n306: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute via `DoMulti`:\n307:   - `DEL session:sess-1`\n308:   - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n309:   - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n310: - **AND** return `nil` error\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n313: - **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n314: - **AND** `limit = 10`\n315: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n316: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n317: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf 1234567890 LIMIT 0 10`\n318: - **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n319: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n322: - **GIVEN** `limit = 0` (or negative)\n323: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n324: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n325: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes skips orphaned entries\n328: - **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains session ID `orphan-1`\n329: - **AND** key `session:orphan-1` does NOT exist (MGET returns empty string)\n330: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n331: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n332: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL skip empty results\n333: - **AND** return only valid sessions\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n336: - **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n337: - **AND** `limit = 10`\n338: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n339: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n340: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf 1234567890 LIMIT 0 10`\n341: - **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n342: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n345: - **GIVEN** `limit = -1` (or zero)\n346: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n347: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n348: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity rejects empty session ID\n351: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n352: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n353: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)` is called\n354: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n355: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity verifies existence\n358: - **GIVEN** session ID `unknown-sess`\n359: - **AND** key `session:unknown-sess` does NOT exist\n360: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n361: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-sess\", now)` is called\n362: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `EXISTS session:unknown-sess`\n363: - **AND** when result is `0`, return `ErrNotFound`\n364: - **AND** SHALL NOT update activity index\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time for zero\n367: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n368: - **AND** `at = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n369: - **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n370: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n371: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n372: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()`\n373: - **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connection\n376: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connection\n377: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n378: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `cli.Close()` on the Valkey client\n379: - **AND** return `nil`\n380: \n381: ---\n382: \n383: ### Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n384: \n385: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Redis address is required\n388: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable is not set\n389: - **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n390: - **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `REDIS_ADDR is required`\n391: - **AND** SHALL NOT create a Redis client\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n394: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n395: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n396: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n397: - **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n398: - **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `REDIS_PASSWORD is required`\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: Redis password can be disabled\n401: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n402: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n403: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n404: - **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n405: - **THEN** the function SHALL succeed\n406: - **AND** create a Redis client with empty password\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Redis password requirement is case-insensitive\n409: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE` (uppercase)\n410: - **WHEN** parsing the option\n411: - **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as disabled\n412: \n413: ---\n414: \n415: ### Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n416: \n417: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n418: \n419: #### Scenario: Valkey address is required\n420: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable is not set\n421: - **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n422: - **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR is required`\n423: - **AND** SHALL NOT create a Valkey client\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Valkey parses comma-separated addresses\n426: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey1:6379,valkey2:6379,valkey3:6379`\n427: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n428: - **THEN** `InitAddress` SHALL be `[\"valkey1:6379\", \"valkey2:6379\", \"valkey3:6379\"]`\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n431: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n432: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n433: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n434: - **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n435: - **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `VALKEY_PASSWORD is required`\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n438: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n439: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n440: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n441: - **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n442: - **THEN** the function SHALL succeed\n443: - **AND** create a Valkey client without password\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true\n446: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n447: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n448: - **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be `true`\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient when VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true\n451: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n452: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n453: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be `true`\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ## Changes to Base Specification\n458: \n459: No modifications to existing interfaces. This AR implements the Store interface defined in AR-012 for Redis and Valkey backends.\n460: \n461: ---\n462: \n463: ## New Interfaces\n464: \n465: ### Redis Store Internal Types\n466: \n467: ```go\n468: // redisOptions holds Redis connection configuration.\n469: type redisOptions struct {\n470:     Addr     string\n471:     Password string\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Valkey Store Internal Types\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: // valkeyOptions holds Valkey connection configuration.\n479: type valkeyOptions struct {\n480:     InitAddress       []string\n481:     Password          string\n482:     DisableCache      bool\n483:     ForceSingleClient bool\n484: }\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ---\n488: \n489: ## Modified Interfaces\n490: \n491: None. This AR implements existing interfaces without modification.\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Behavioral Changes\n496: \n497: | Behavior | Before | After |\n498: |----------|--------|-------|\n499: | Redis Store | Interface only | Full Redis implementation in `redis.go` |\n500: | Valkey Store | Interface only | Full Valkey implementation in `valkey.go` |\n501: | Connection management | None | Redis client with pooling via go-redis/v9 |\n502: | Connection management | None | Valkey client via valkey-go |\n503: | Command execution | None | Full Redis command support via Pipeline |\n504: | Command execution | None | Full Valkey command support via DoMulti |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Dependencies\n509: \n510: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n511: |------------|---------|---------|\n512: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client for Go |\n513: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Valkey client for Go |\n514: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Store interface definition |\n515: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo type definition |\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## File Index\n520: \n521: | Path | Purpose |\n522: |------|---------|\n523: | `pkg/store/redis.go` | Redis Store implementation |\n524: | `pkg/store/valkey.go` | Valkey Store implementation |\n525: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Provider selection and initialization |\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Constants\n530: \n531: | Constant | Value | Description |\n532: |----------|-------|-------------|\n533: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n534: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n535: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n536: \n537: ---\n538: \n539: ## Environment Variables\n540: \n541: ### Redis Configuration\n542: \n543: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n544: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n545: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n546: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Redis authentication password |\n547: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n548: \n549: ### Valkey Configuration\n550: \n551: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n552: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n553: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated Valkey addresses |\n554: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Valkey authentication password |\n555: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n556: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client cache |\n557: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` for single client mode |\n558: \n559: *Required unless the corresponding `_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `false`\n560: \n561: ---\n562: \n563: ## API Endpoints Summary\n564: \n565: This AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n566: \n567: ---\n568: \n569: ## Migration Notes\n570: \n571: - **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` and `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` to go.mod\n572: - **Environment setup**: Configure `REDIS_ADDR` or `VALKEY_ADDR` before deployment\n573: - **File naming**: Implementation files are `redis.go` and `valkey.go` (not `store_redis.go`/`store_valkey.go`)\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n578: \n579: 1. **Redis Implementation Completeness**: All Store interface methods implemented for Redis\n580: 2. **Valkey Implementation Completeness**: All Store interface methods implemented for Valkey\n581: 3. **Error Handling**: Redis/Valkey errors properly translated to store errors (ErrNotFound)\n582: 4. **Atomicity**: Pipeline operations ensure atomic writes for StoreSandbox and Delete\n583: 5. **Index Management**: ZSET indexes maintained correctly for both backends\n584: 6. **Connection Management**: Proper client lifecycle handling for both Redis and Valkey\n585: 7. **Environment Validation**: Required environment variables validated at initialization\n586: 8. **Test Coverage**: Unit and integration tests pass for both implementations\n\n(End of file - total 586 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides concrete implementations of the Store interface using Redis and Valkey as backends. It handles connection management, command execution, and backend-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Redis-backed Store implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` that satisfies the Store interface.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871320191,"end":1775871320215}}}}
