{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871537182,"sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2e7efd001DUWECc6cWH0R41","messageID":"msg_d7a2e53a1001mYqZXfNoAQosnz","sessionID":"ses_285d26c42ffeRiRhL7DEy1Gadr","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-015  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe PicoD Command Execution API provides a high-level interface for executing commands in sandbox environments. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution, with features including resource limits, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CommandExecutor Interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `CommandExecutor` interface that supports synchronous execution, asynchronous execution, status retrieval, cancellation, and output streaming.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute runs command synchronously\n- **GIVEN** a valid `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **AND** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"echo\"`, `Args=[\"hello\"]`\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL validate the request\n- **AND** execute the command in the sandbox\n- **AND** capture stdout and stderr\n- **AND** return an `ExecutionResult` with `ExitCode=0`, `Stdout=[]byte(\"hello\\n\")`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on successful execution\n\n#### Scenario: Execute returns error on invalid request\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with empty `Command=\"\"`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating command is required\n- **AND** SHALL NOT attempt sandbox execution\n\n#### Scenario: Execute returns error on timeout\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"sleep\"`, `Args=[\"60\"]`, `Timeout=1s`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL start the command\n- **AND** when timeout expires, cancel the execution\n- **AND** return an error indicating timeout occurred\n- **AND** the result SHALL have `Status.State=StateFailed`\n\n#### Scenario: ExecuteAsync queues command for background execution\n- **GIVEN** a valid `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"long-running-task\"`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL generate a unique `ExecutionID`\n- **AND** persist initial status with `State=StatePending`\n- **AND** queue the execution for background processing\n- **AND** return the `ExecutionID` immediately\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: ExecuteAsync validates request before queuing\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `WorkingDir=\"/nonexistent/path\"`\n- **AND** the working directory does not exist in sandbox\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL validate the request\n- **AND** return an error indicating working directory is invalid\n- **AND** SHALL NOT queue the execution\n\n#### Scenario: GetStatus returns current execution status\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-abc123\"` exists with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL query the status store\n- **AND** return an `ExecutionStatus` with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: GetStatus returns completed status\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-completed\"` has finished with exit code 0\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-completed\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ExecutionStatus` with:\n  - `State=StateCompleted`\n  - `ExitCode=*0` (pointer to 0)\n  - `FinishedAt` set to completion time\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: GetStatus returns error for non-existent execution\n- **GIVEN** no execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-nonexistent\"` exists\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-nonexistent\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Cancel stops a running execution\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-running\"` with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, \"exec-running\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL signal the sandbox to terminate the process\n- **AND** update status to `State=StateCancelled`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Cancel returns error for already completed execution\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-done\"` with `State=StateCompleted`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, \"exec-done\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete`\n\n#### Scenario: StreamOutput returns output channel for running execution\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-streaming\"` with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** the execution is producing output\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `StreamOutput(ctx, \"exec-streaming\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a `<-chan OutputChunk` channel\n- **AND** the channel SHALL receive chunks as output is produced\n- **AND** the channel SHALL be closed when execution completes\n\n#### Scenario: StreamOutput returns error for non-existent execution\n- **GIVEN** no execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-missing\"` exists\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `StreamOutput(ctx, \"exec-missing\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionNotFound`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ExecutionRequest Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate `ExecutionRequest` fields and reject invalid configurations before execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Empty command is rejected\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"\"`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** any execution method is called with this request\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidCommand: command is required`\n\n#### Scenario: Command with path traversal is rejected\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"../../../etc/passwd\"`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error indicating command contains invalid characters\n\n#### Scenario: WorkingDir outside allowed paths is rejected\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `WorkingDir=\"/etc\"`\n- **AND** allowed working directories are restricted to `/workspace/*`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidWorkingDir: working directory not allowed`\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variable names are validated\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Environment={\"INVALID-NAME\": \"value\"}`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error indicating invalid environment variable name\n\n#### Scenario: SessionID is required for sandbox resolution\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `SessionID=\"\"`\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidSessionID: session ID is required`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Resource Constraints Enforcement\n\nThe system SHALL enforce resource limits on command executions through sandbox integration.\n\n#### Scenario: Memory limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxMemory=104857600` (100MB)\n- **AND** the command attempts to allocate 200MB\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL enforce the memory limit\n- **AND** the execution SHALL be terminated with `ExitCode != 0`\n- **AND** the result SHALL have `Error.Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CPU limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxCPU=50.0` (50%)\n- **AND** the command is CPU-intensive\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL throttle CPU usage to 50%\n- **AND** execution SHALL complete within timeout\n\n#### Scenario: File descriptor limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxFiles=10`\n- **AND** the command attempts to open 20 files\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL return error on file open exceeding limit\n- **AND** `Error.Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"` with details about file limit\n\n#### Scenario: IO bandwidth limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxIOBytes=1048576` (1MB/s)\n- **AND** the command performs heavy IO operations\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL throttle IO to 1MB/s\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Execution Status Management\n\nThe system SHALL maintain execution status through state transitions and persist status in the store.\n\n#### Scenario: Status transitions from pending to running\n- **GIVEN** an async execution is queued with `State=StatePending`\n- **WHEN** the background worker picks up the execution\n- **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** `StartedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n\n#### Scenario: Status transitions from running to completed\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** the command completes with exit code 0\n- **WHEN** the execution finishes\n- **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateCompleted`\n- **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be set to 0\n- **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n\n#### Scenario: Status transitions from running to failed\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n- **AND** the command exits with non-zero code\n- **WHEN** the execution finishes\n- **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateFailed`\n- **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be set to the actual exit code\n- **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n- **AND** `Error` SHALL contain failure details\n\n#### Scenario: Status transitions to cancelled\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n- **WHEN** `Cancel()` is called\n- **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateCancelled`\n- **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to cancellation time\n- **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be nil or reflect termination signal\n\n#### Scenario: Terminal states are immutable\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateCompleted`\n- **WHEN** any status update is attempted\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL reject the update\n- **AND** return error indicating execution is in terminal state\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Output Capture and Streaming\n\nThe system SHALL capture command output (stdout/stderr) and support real-time streaming.\n\n#### Scenario: Output is captured for sync execution\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"echo\"`, `Args=[\"stdout\"]`, stdout redirected\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the `ExecutionResult.Stdout` SHALL contain `[]byte(\"stdout\\n\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Stderr is captured separately\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` that writes to stderr\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the `ExecutionResult.Stderr` SHALL contain the error output\n- **AND** `ExecutionResult.Stdout` SHALL be empty or contain stdout only\n\n#### Scenario: Output size limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** configuration `max_output_size=1MB`\n- **AND** a command that produces 10MB of output\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** output capture SHALL be truncated at 1MB\n- **AND** `ExecutionResult` SHALL indicate truncation occurred\n\n#### Scenario: StreamOutput delivers chunks in order\n- **GIVEN** an async execution is running and producing output\n- **AND** a client calls `StreamOutput(ctx, id)`\n- **WHEN** the command writes \"line1\\nline2\\n\"\n- **THEN** the channel SHALL receive `OutputChunk{Data: []byte(\"line1\\n\"), Type: Stdout}`\n- **AND** then `OutputChunk{Data: []byte(\"line2\\n\"), Type: Stdout}`\n- **AND** chunks SHALL be in order of production\n\n#### Scenario: StreamOutput context cancellation stops streaming\n- **GIVEN** a client is streaming output from an execution\n- **AND** the client cancels the context\n- **WHEN** the context cancellation is detected\n- **THEN** the output channel SHALL be closed\n- **AND** the streaming goroutine SHALL exit cleanly\n\n#### Scenario: Output buffering respects buffer size limits\n- **GIVEN** configuration `output_buffer_size=4KB`\n- **AND** a command producing continuous output\n- **WHEN** output exceeds 4KB\n- **THEN** older output SHALL be discarded or flushed to store\n- **AND** buffer SHALL not exceed configured size\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling and Error Types\n\nThe system SHALL define and return appropriate error types for different failure scenarios.\n\n#### Scenario: ErrInvalidRequest for malformed requests\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with invalid fields\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrInvalidRequest`\n- **AND** the error message SHALL describe which field is invalid\n\n#### Scenario: ErrResourceExceeded for resource limit violations\n- **GIVEN** an execution that exceeds memory limits\n- **WHEN** the sandbox terminates the process\n- **THEN** the result SHALL contain `Error` with `Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"`\n- **AND** `Error.Message` SHALL indicate which resource was exceeded\n\n#### Scenario: ErrTimeout for execution timeout\n- **GIVEN** an execution with `Timeout=5s`\n- **AND** the command runs longer than 5 seconds\n- **WHEN** timeout occurs\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrTimeout`\n- **AND** `ExecutionStatus.State` SHALL be `StateFailed`\n\n#### Scenario: ErrSandboxUnavailable when sandbox is not accessible\n- **GIVEN** a `SessionID` that resolves to an unreachable sandbox\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrSandboxUnavailable`\n- **AND** the error SHALL include sandbox identification details\n\n#### Scenario: ErrExecutionFailed for non-zero exit codes\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` completes\n- **THEN** the result SHALL have `ExitCode=1`\n- **AND** the error SHALL be `ErrExecutionFailed` with exit code in details\n\n#### Scenario: ErrCancelled for cancelled executions\n- **GIVEN** a running execution\n- **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, id)` is called\n- **THEN** the status SHALL be `StateCancelled`\n- **AND** subsequent calls to `GetStatus` SHALL indicate cancellation\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration with Sandbox Interface\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with the sandbox interface (AR-009) for actual command execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox is resolved by SessionID\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"`\n- **AND** session `\"sess-abc123\"` exists in the store with sandbox info\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL query the store for sandbox info\n- **AND** resolve the sandbox endpoint from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox connection failures are handled\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SessionID` pointing to a sandbox\n- **AND** the sandbox pod is not responding\n- **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrSandboxUnavailable`\n- **AND** the error SHALL include the connection failure reason\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox environment variables are merged\n- **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Environment={\"FOO\": \"bar\"}`\n- **AND** the sandbox has default environment variables\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the request environment SHALL override sandbox defaults\n- **AND** merged environment SHALL be passed to the sandbox\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration with Status Store\n\nThe system SHALL persist execution status and metadata using the store interface (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014).\n\n#### Scenario: Execution status is persisted on state change\n- **GIVEN** an async execution transitions from `StatePending` to `StateRunning`\n- **WHEN** the state change occurs\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `store.UpdateStatus(ctx, status)`\n- **AND** the update SHALL succeed before acknowledging the transition\n\n#### Scenario: Store failures are handled gracefully\n- **GIVEN** an execution completes successfully\n- **AND** the store is temporarily unavailable\n- **WHEN** status update is attempted\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL log the error\n- **AND** return the execution result to the caller\n- **AND** status MAY be inconsistent (documented limitation)\n\n#### Scenario: Output is stored for later retrieval\n- **GIVEN** a completed execution with captured output\n- **WHEN** the execution finishes\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL store output in the store\n- **AND** subsequent `GetStatus` calls SHALL include output reference\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ExecutionID Generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate unique execution identifiers for tracking.\n\n#### Scenario: ExecutionID is unique per execution\n- **GIVEN** multiple `ExecuteAsync` calls\n- **WHEN** each call returns an `ExecutionID`\n- **THEN** all returned IDs SHALL be unique\n- **AND** no two executions SHALL share the same ID\n\n#### Scenario: ExecutionID format is valid\n- **GIVEN** an execution is queued\n- **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync` returns\n- **THEN** the `ExecutionID` SHALL match pattern `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`\n- **AND** length SHALL be between 8 and 64 characters\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Context Cancellation Handling\n\nThe system SHALL respect context cancellation and clean up resources appropriately.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute cancels on context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is running\n- **AND** the context is cancelled\n- **WHEN** cancellation is detected\n- **THEN** the execution SHALL be terminated\n- **AND** error `ErrCancelled` SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: GetStatus returns error on cancelled context\n- **GIVEN** a cancelled context\n- **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, id)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return the context error\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query the store\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup on context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** an async execution is streaming output\n- **AND** the context is cancelled\n- **WHEN** cancellation propagates\n- **THEN** all goroutines SHALL exit\n- **AND** channels SHALL be closed\n- **AND** no goroutine leaks SHALL occur\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Concurrent Execution Limits\n\nThe system SHALL enforce limits on concurrent command executions.\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent limit is enforced\n- **GIVEN** configuration `max_concurrent_executions=10`\n- **AND** 10 executions are currently running\n- **WHEN** an 11th execution is requested\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL queue the request\n- **OR** return `ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions`\n\n#### Scenario: Queued execution starts when slot available\n- **GIVEN** `max_concurrent_executions=5`\n- **AND** 5 executions are running\n- **AND** 3 executions are queued\n- **WHEN** one running execution completes\n- **THEN** the first queued execution SHALL start\n- **AND** its status SHALL transition to `StateRunning`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL read PicoD configuration from environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout is applied\n- **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=30s`\n- **AND** an `ExecutionRequest` with no `Timeout` set\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** the default timeout of 30s SHALL be applied\n\n#### Scenario: Max output size is configurable\n- **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE=5MB`\n- **AND** a command producing large output\n- **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n- **THEN** output SHALL be limited to 5MB\n\n#### Scenario: Max concurrent executions is configurable\n- **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT=50`\n- **WHEN** the `CommandExecutor` is initialized\n- **THEN** the concurrent execution limit SHALL be set to 50\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nNo modifications to existing interfaces. This AR introduces new functionality in the `pkg/picod` module.\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### CommandExecutor Interface\n\n```go\npackage picod\n\nimport \"context\"\n\n// CommandExecutor defines the interface for executing commands in sandboxes.\ntype CommandExecutor interface {\n    // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n    \n    // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n    ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n    \n    // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n    GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n    \n    // Cancel stops a running execution.\n    Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n    \n    // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n    StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Execution Types\n\n```go\n// ExecutionID uniquely identifies a command execution.\ntype ExecutionID string\n\n// ExecutionRequest contains parameters for command execution.\ntype ExecutionRequest struct {\n    Command        string\n    Args           []string\n    WorkingDir     string\n    Environment    map[string]string\n    Timeout        time.Duration\n    ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n    SessionID      string\n}\n\n// ExecutionResult contains the result of a command execution.\ntype ExecutionResult struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    Status     ExecutionStatus\n    ExitCode   int\n    Stdout     []byte\n    Stderr     []byte\n    StartedAt  time.Time\n    FinishedAt time.Time\n    Error      *ExecutionError\n}\n\n// ExecutionStatus represents the current state of an execution.\ntype ExecutionStatus struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    State      ExecutionState\n    StartedAt  *time.Time\n    FinishedAt *time.Time\n    ExitCode   *int\n}\n\n// ExecutionState represents the state of command execution.\ntype ExecutionState string\n\nconst (\n    StatePending   ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n    StateRunning   ExecutionState = \"running\"\n    StateCompleted ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n    StateFailed    ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n    StateCancelled ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\n// ResourceConstraints defines resource limits for execution.\ntype ResourceConstraints struct {\n    MaxMemory  int64   // bytes\n    MaxCPU     float64 // percentage (0-100)\n    MaxIOBytes int64   // bytes per second\n    MaxFiles   int     // max open file descriptors\n}\n\n// ExecutionError contains detailed error information.\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Details map[string]interface{}\n}\n\n// OutputChunk represents a piece of output from a command.\ntype OutputChunk struct {\n    Data      []byte\n    Type      OutputType\n    Timestamp time.Time\n}\n\n// OutputType indicates the source of output.\ntype OutputType string\n\nconst (\n    Stdout OutputType = \"stdout\"\n    Stderr OutputType = \"stderr\"\n)\n\n// ExecutorOptions contains configuration for CommandExecutor.\ntype ExecutorOptions struct {\n    DefaultTimeout         time.Duration\n    MaxConcurrentExecutions int\n    MaxOutputSize          int64\n    OutputBufferSize       int\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrInvalidRequest               = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n    ErrInvalidCommand               = errors.New(\"picod: command is required\")\n    ErrInvalidSessionID             = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n    ErrInvalidWorkingDir            = errors.New(\"picod: invalid working directory\")\n    ErrResourceExceeded             = errors.New(\"picod: resource limits exceeded\")\n    ErrTimeout                      = errors.New(\"picod: execution timeout\")\n    ErrSandboxUnavailable           = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n    ErrExecutionFailed              = errors.New(\"picod: execution failed\")\n    ErrExecutionNotFound            = errors.New(\"picod: execution not found\")\n    ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete     = errors.New(\"picod: execution already complete\")\n    ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions  = errors.New(\"picod: too many concurrent executions\")\n    ErrCancelled                    = errors.New(\"picod: execution cancelled\")\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\nNone. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Command execution | Direct sandbox calls | Through PicoD API with resource limits |\n| Execution tracking | No persistence | Persistent status in store |\n| Output handling | Direct capture | Buffered, size-limited capture |\n| Cancellation | Not supported | Supported via Cancel() API |\n| Streaming | Not supported | Real-time output streaming |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox` | Local | Sandbox interface (AR-009) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Status persistence (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | Shared types |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | ExecutionID generation |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/picod/executor.go` | CommandExecutor implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` | Unit tests |\n| `pkg/picod/types.go` | Request/response type definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/status.go` | Execution status management |\n| `pkg/picod/output.go` | Output capture and streaming |\n| `pkg/picod/errors.go` | Error type definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/validation.go` | Request validation logic |\n\n---\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `defaultTimeout` | `30s` | Default execution timeout |\n| `maxConcurrentDefault` | `100` | Default concurrent execution limit |\n| `maxOutputSizeDefault` | `10MB` | Default max output capture size |\n| `outputBufferSizeDefault` | `4KB` | Default output buffer size |\n| `executionIDLength` | `16` | Length of generated execution IDs |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default timeout for command execution |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT` | No | `100` | Maximum concurrent executions |\n| `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Maximum output capture size |\n| `PICOD_OUTPUT_BUFFER_SIZE` | No | `4KB` | Output buffer size for streaming |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\nThis AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Workload Manager | Execute commands in sandboxes |\n| CLI Toolkit | Synchronous command execution |\n| Integration Layer | Async execution with streaming |\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/google/uuid` to go.mod\n- **Store dependency**: Requires working store (Redis/Valkey) for status persistence\n- **Sandbox dependency**: Requires functional sandbox interface (AR-009)\n- **No breaking changes**: PicoD API is additive layer on existing components\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Interface Completeness**: All CommandExecutor methods implemented\n2. **Request Validation**: Invalid requests rejected before execution\n3. **Resource Enforcement**: Resource limits enforced via sandbox integration\n4. **Status Tracking**: State transitions persisted correctly\n5. **Output Handling**: Stdout/stderr captured and streamable\n6. **Cancellation**: Running executions can be cancelled\n7. **Error Types**: Appropriate errors returned for each failure mode\n8. **Context Handling**: Respects context cancellation\n9. **Concurrency Limits**: Enforced and queued correctly\n10. **Integration**: Works with sandbox (AR-009) and store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871537124,"end":1775871537178}}}}
